AgentForce Infotech Database Access and Management

## Getting Database Access

1. Request access through AgentForce IT Service Portal: https://itportal.agentforce.internal
2. Fill out the "Database Access Request" form
3. Specify which databases you need:
   - Development (phoenix-dev)
   - Staging (phoenix-staging)
   - Production (phoenix-prod) - requires manager approval
4. Wait for approval (usually within 24 hours, urgent requests contact DBA directly)
5. You'll receive credentials via encrypted email from database@agentforce.com

## Connection Details

**Development Database (PostgreSQL 15):**
- Host: db-dev.agentforce.internal
- Port: 5432
- Database: phoenix_dev
- Username: {your-email}@agentforce.com
- Use your personal credentials (provided via email)

**Staging Database:**
- Host: db-staging.agentforce.internal
- Port: 5432
- Database: phoenix_staging
- Read-only access for most developers
- Write access requires special approval from DBA (contact Ravi Verma)

**Production Database:**
- Host: db-prod.agentforce.internal
- Port: 5432
- Database: phoenix_prod
- Read-only access only (via read replica)
- Write access requires DBA approval (Ravi Verma) and Jira change request
- Production writes only through application, never direct SQL

## Tools

- **DBeaver**: Recommended for database management (download from IT portal)
- **pgAdmin**: Alternative option (pre-installed on company laptops)
- Connection strings stored in AgentForce 1Password vault (team: "Database Credentials")
- Never commit database credentials to GitLab

## Best Practices at AgentForce

- Always use parameterized queries (prevent SQL injection)
- Test queries on dev database before running on staging/prod
- Backup data before major schema changes
- Document schema changes in Django migration files (for backend) or migration scripts
- Use database transactions for multi-step operations
- Never run DROP or TRUNCATE on staging/prod without DBA approval
- Use connection pooling (already configured in application)

## Database Team Contacts

- DBA Lead: Ravi Verma (ravi.verma@agentforce.com, ext 3012)
- Database Support: database@agentforce.com
- Slack: #agentforce-database-support channel

For urgent access, contact Ravi Verma directly or ping in #agentforce-database-support.
